   M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/src/trusted/validator_arm/gen/arm32_decode_named_bases.h?r1=10663&amp;r2=10662&amp;pathrev=10663

Add type checking of decoder fields during parsing, to simplify bug finding.

This fixes a problem where parsed decoder fields are not translated
until after parsing is done. As a result, mistyped field values will
generate errors at a time where the translator doesn't know the
source.

To fix this problem, we turn on type checking at parse time, when
decoder fields are set. At that time, we go ahead and translate the
corresponding value using the (type converting) translation function
that will be used when they are translated. This will allow exceptions
to be caught by the parser and reported at the source line that caused
the exception.

BUG= http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3111
